{"lemma":"تِبْنِ","slug":"تِبْنِ","root":"ت.ب.ن","root_slug":"ت-ب-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ب-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":12,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3761","n3762","n3764","n3765","n3766"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَبَنَّى (tabannā) (form V)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"adoption"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"straw; hay","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give straw to, to feed with straw; to sell straw"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feed with straw"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bung, to cork"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَبَنَ (tabana, “to give straw to”)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a great bowl that can satisfy the thirst of twenty, a vessel used to fill drinking cups"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a generous chieftain, one who gives large amounts"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a wolf for its thirst for blood being likened to a great vessel's amount"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be sagacious, to be callid, to be skillful in knowing, to be minute in inspection"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"intelligent, callid, sagacious, skillful in knowing, minute in inspection"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَبِنَ (tabina, “to be callid”)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Likely borrowed from Aramaic תִּבְנָא / ܬܒܢܐ (teḇnā, “straw”), which is suspected mainly because of the varying vocalization, and also because this root is underdeveloped or it has the unrelated meaning of a “bowl”. The Aramaic might in turn come from Akkadian 𒅔𒉡𒁕 (/⁠tibnu⁠/, “straw”) but can likewise be cognate. Else the word is only present in Hebrew תֶּבֶן (teḇen, “straw”), in which language there is nothing to relate to either.\n\nDenominal verb of تِبْن (tibn, “straw”). In the “to bung” sense allegedly motivated by Spanish taponar.\n\nUncertain with possible connection to Akkadian 𒋰𒉌𒌈 (/⁠tabnītu⁠/, “an offering basket, a place to deposit tribute to a ruler or offerings before deities”, literally “well-arranged, well-made or constructed”) and Akkadian 𒁀𒀀𒉡 (/⁠bānu⁠/, “a ewer, vessel that fills up other vessels”, literally “that which does what it was made for; a by-name for a ewer in ritual texts”), therefore distantly being connected to ب ن ي (b n y).\n\nLike the more productive root ط ب ن (ṭ b n), from which there is with the like meanings طَبِنَ (ṭabina) and طَبِن (ṭabin)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3761","headword_ar":"تَبَنَ","root":"tbn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabonN","text_ar":"تَبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a beast"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tibon","text_ar":"تِبْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, M, K.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sold"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tibon","text_ar":"تِبْن"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straw."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabina","text_ar":"تَبِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabanN","text_ar":"تَبَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabonN","text_ar":"تَبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAnapN","text_ar":"تَبَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, * M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAniyapN","text_ar":"تَبَانِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, intelligent, sagacious, skilful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTina","text_ar":"فَطِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra faTinFA","text_ar":"صَارَ فَطِنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and nice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minute, in inspection"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAnapN","text_ar":"تَبَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being very intelligent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sagacious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing, and nice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minute, in inspection;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaAnahN","text_ar":"طَبَانَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; accord. to AO and AA: (T:) these two words signify the same (T, S, M *) accord. to [most of] the leading authorities: (T:) and Yaakoob asserts that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) [or the reverse seems to be the case in the opinion of Az, who here remarks that there are many instances of the change of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, in good: (M:) or, accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabina","text_ar":"طَبِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means in evil; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabina","text_ar":"تَبِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that he makes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TbAnp","text_ar":"طبانة"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be in deceiving, or beguiling, and suddenly, or unexpectedly, attacking or destroying: but En-Nadr says the contr.; and accord. to him,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabanN","text_ar":"طَبَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the having knowledge of affairs, and intelligence, or sagacity, and science: (T:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tb~n","text_ar":"تبّن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatobiynN","text_ar":"تَتْبِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabina","text_ar":"تَبِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he inspected nicely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minutely:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in a trad. in which it is said, respecting a woman whose husband has died leaving her pregnant,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yunofaqu EalayohaA mino jamiyEi AlmaAli Hat~aY tab~anotumo","text_ar":"يُنْفَقُ عَلَيْهَا مِنْ جَمِيعِ المَالِ حَتَّى تَبَّنْتُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA tab~anotumo","text_ar":"مَا تَبَّنْتُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She shall be expended upon from the whole of the property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until ye make a nice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minute, inspection"},{"kind":"text","text":"[into the circumstances of the case], and say otherwise, (T, S,) i. e., that she shall be expended upon from her own share: (T:) and so in another trad., in which it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Alr~ajula layatakal~amu biAlkalimapi yutab~inu fiyhaA yahowiY bihaA fiY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الرَّجُلَ لَيَتَكَلَّمُ بِالكَلِمَةِ يُتَبِّنُ فِيهَا يَهْوِى بِهَا فِى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A 'Obeyd, T, M,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily a man will say a saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which he will be nice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minute"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in expression,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby he will fall into the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Hell]: (TA:) here A 'Obeyd thinks the meaning to be the making language obscure, or abstruse, and disputing in a matter of religion. (T.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabina lahu","text_ar":"تَبِنَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He understood it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knew it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was cognizant, of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabina","text_ar":"طَبِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","T","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n3762","headword_ar":"تبّن","root":"tbn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatobiynN","text_ar":"تَتْبِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabon~hu","text_ar":"تَبْنّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as before,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clad him with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~aAn","text_ar":"تُبَّان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3764","headword_ar":"تَبْنٌ","root":"tbn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3765","headword_ar":"تِبْنٌ","root":"tbn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabonN","text_ar":"تَبْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Straw;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stalks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stems,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiyf","text_ar":"عَصِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, K,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stalk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stem,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAq","text_ar":"سَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of seed-produce,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as wheat and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) [generally]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after it has been trodden"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrashed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cut"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheat when it has been trodden"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrashed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cut"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the feet of beasts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by repeatedly drawing over it the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"machine called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midowas","text_ar":"مِدْوَس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dws","text_ar":"دوس"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [a coll. gen. n.:] n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a straw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of straw"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqal~u mino tibonapK","text_ar":"اَقَلُّ مِنْ تِبْنَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Less than a straw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of straw"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  Also, the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great bowl:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bowl that satisfies the thirst of twenty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatest of bowls, that almost satisfies the thirst of twenty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, M:) next is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHon","text_ar":"صَحْن"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is nearly equal thereto: then, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eus~","text_ar":"عُسّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", that satisfies the thirst of three and of four: then, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadaH","text_ar":"قَدَح"},{"kind":"text","text":", that satisfies the thirst of two men: then, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEob","text_ar":"قَعْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", that satisfies the thirst of one man: then, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gumar","text_ar":"غُمَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ks, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bowl of rude,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough, make; not made neatly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilfully."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, probably,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A liberal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bountiful, and noble, chief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wolf."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","Msb","S","Ks"]},{"entry_id":"n3766","headword_ar":"تَبِنٌ","root":"tbn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intelligent, sagacious, skilful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing; and nice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minute, in inspection"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into affairs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabinN","text_ar":"طَبِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very intelligent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabina","text_ar":"تَبِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  And One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who plays with his hand with everything."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}